The President recently met with his national security team to discuss efforts to protect the American people during the holiday season. He praised the cooperation between federal, state, and local authorities and directed agencies to remain vigilant in preventing attacks by individuals radicalized to violence. The President was also briefed on successful military operations against ISIL and al-Qa'ida and instructed the Department of Defense and the Intelligence Community to continue pressuring terrorists. He expressed gratitude for U.S. personnel deployed worldwide and security personnel at borders, ports, and facilities across the nation during the holidays.